section.p:
Here are some common table use-cases and the CSS selectors for customizing them. These
        example uses the background-color CSS property but any CSS property can be
        used (border, margin, padding, etc.).

Select all non-header
            cells:*[class ~= "topic/tbody"] *[class ~= "topic/entry"] {
  background-color: lightgray;
}

Select some table rows (using :nth-of-type()
            pseudo-class):/* Select all even rows. */
*[class ~= "topic/tbody"] *[class ~= "topic/row"]:nth-of-type(even) {
  background-color: lightgray;
}
/* Select the fourth row. */
*[class ~= "topic/tbody"] *[class ~= "topic/row"]:nth-of-type(4) {
  background-color: yellow;
}

Select specific table columns (using :nth-of-type()
            pseudo-class):/* Select all odd columns. */
*[class ~= "topic/tbody"] *[class ~= "topic/entry"]:nth-of-type(odd) {
  background-color: lightgray;
}
/* Select the second column. */
*[class ~= "topic/tbody"] *[class ~= "topic/entry"]:nth-of-type(2) {
  background-color: yellow;
}
